25/* Processor specific flags for the ELF header e_flags field. */
26#define EF_ARM_RELEXEC 0x01
27#define EF_ARM_INTERWORK 0x04
28#define EF_ARM_APCS_26 0x08
29#define EF_ARM_APCS_FLOAT 0x10
30#define EF_ARM_PIC 0x20
31#define EF_ARM_ALIGN8 0x40 /* 8-bit structure alignment is in use. */
32#define EF_ARM_NEW_ABI 0x80
33#define EF_ARM_OLD_ABI 0x100
34#define EF_ARM_SOFT_FLOAT 0x200
35#define EF_ARM_VFP_FLOAT 0x400
36#define EF_ARM_MAVERICK_FLOAT 0x800
37
38/* Frame unwind information */
39#define PT_ARM_EXIDX (PT_LOPROC + 1)
40
41/* Other constants defined in the ARM ELF spec. version B-01. */
42#define EF_ARM_SYMSARESORTED 0x04 /* NB conflicts with EF_INTERWORK. */
43#define EF_ARM_DYNSYMSUSESEGIDX 0x08 /* NB conflicts with EF_APCS26. */
44#define EF_ARM_MAPSYMSFIRST 0x10 /* NB conflicts with EF_APCS_FLOAT. */
45#define EF_ARM_EABIMASK 0xFF000000
46
47/* New constants defined in the ARM ELF spec. version XXX.
48 Only valid in conjunction with EF_ARM_EABI_VER5. */
49#define EF_ARM_ABI_FLOAT_SOFT 0x200 /* NB conflicts with EF_ARM_SOFT_FLOAT. */
50#define EF_ARM_ABI_FLOAT_HARD 0x400 /* NB conflicts with EF_ARM_VFP_FLOAT. */
51
52/* Constants defined in AAELF. */
53#define EF_ARM_BE8 0x00800000
54#define EF_ARM_LE8 0x00400000
55
56#define EF_ARM_EABI_VERSION(flags) ((flags) & EF_ARM_EABIMASK)
57#define EF_ARM_EABI_UNKNOWN 0x00000000
58#define EF_ARM_EABI_VER1 0x01000000
59#define EF_ARM_EABI_VER2 0x02000000
60#define EF_ARM_EABI_VER3 0x03000000
61#define EF_ARM_EABI_VER4 0x04000000
62#define EF_ARM_EABI_VER5 0x05000000
63
64/* Local aliases for some flags to match names used by COFF port. */
65#define F_INTERWORK EF_ARM_INTERWORK
66#define F_APCS26 EF_ARM_APCS_26
67#define F_APCS_FLOAT EF_ARM_APCS_FLOAT
68#define F_PIC EF_ARM_PIC
69#define F_SOFT_FLOAT EF_ARM_SOFT_FLOAT
70#define F_VFP_FLOAT EF_ARM_VFP_FLOAT
71
72/* Additional symbol types for Thumb. */
73#define STT_ARM_TFUNC STT_LOPROC /* A Thumb function. */
74#define STT_ARM_16BIT STT_HIPROC /* A Thumb label. */
75
76/* Additional section types. */
77#define SHT_ARM_EXIDX 0x70000001 /* Section holds ARM unwind info. */
78#define SHT_ARM_PREEMPTMAP 0x70000002 /* Section pre-emption details. */
79#define SHT_ARM_ATTRIBUTES 0x70000003 /* Section holds attributes. */
80#define SHT_ARM_DEBUGOVERLAY 0x70000004 /* Section holds overlay debug info. */
81#define SHT_ARM_OVERLAYSECTION 0x70000005 /* Section holds GDB and overlay integration info. */
82
83/* ARM-specific values for sh_flags. */
84#define SHF_ENTRYSECT 0x10000000 /* Section contains an entry point. */
85#define SHF_ARM_PURECODE 0x20000000 /* Section contains only code and no data. */
86#define SHF_COMDEF 0x80000000 /* Section may be multiply defined in the input to a link step. */
87
88/* ARM-specific program header flags. */
89#define PF_ARM_SB 0x10000000 /* Segment contains the location addressed by the static base. */
90#define PF_ARM_PI 0x20000000 /* Segment is position-independent. */
91#define PF_ARM_ABS 0x40000000 /* Segment must be loaded at its base address. */
92

94#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_PRE_V4 0
95#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V4 1
96#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V4T 2
97#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V5T 3
98#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V5TE 4
99#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V5TEJ 5
100#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V6 6
101#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V6KZ 7
102#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V6T2 8
103#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V6K 9
104#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V7 10
105#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V6_M 11
106#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V6S_M 12
107#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V7E_M 13
108#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V8 14
109#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V8R 15
110#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V8M_BASE 16
111#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V8M_MAIN 17
112#define MAX_TAG_CPU_ARCH TAG_CPU_ARCH_V8M_MAIN
113/* Pseudo-architecture to allow objects to be compatible with the subset of
114 armv4t and armv6-m. This value should never be stored in object files. */
115#define TAG_CPU_ARCH_V4T_PLUS_V6_M (MAX_TAG_CPU_ARCH + 1)

366enum arm_st_branch_type {
367 ST_BRANCH_TO_ARM,
368 ST_BRANCH_TO_THUMB,
369 ST_BRANCH_LONG,
370 ST_BRANCH_UNKNOWN,
371 ST_BRANCH_ENUM_SIZE
372};
373
374#define NUM_ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITS 2
375#define ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITMASK \
376 ((1 << NUM_ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITS) - 1)
377
378#define ARM_GET_SYM_BRANCH_TYPE(STI) \
379 ((enum arm_st_branch_type) ((STI) & ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITMASK))
380#ifdef BFD_ASSERT
381#define ARM_SET_SYM_BRANCH_TYPE(STI, TYPE) \
382 do { \
383 BFD_ASSERT (TYPE <= ST_BRANCH_ENUM_SIZE); \
384 BFD_ASSERT ((1 << NUM_ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITS) \
385 >= ST_BRANCH_ENUM_SIZE); \
386 (STI) = (((STI) & ~ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITMASK) \
387 | ((TYPE) & ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITMASK)); \
388 } while (0)
389#else
390#define ARM_SET_SYM_BRANCH_TYPE(STI, TYPE) \
391 (STI) = (((STI) & ~ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITMASK) \
392 | ((TYPE) & ENUM_ARM_ST_BRANCH_TYPE_BITMASK))
393#endif
394
395/* Get or set whether a symbol is a special symbol of an entry function of CMSE
396 secure code. */
397#define ARM_GET_SYM_CMSE_SPCL(SYM_TARGET_INTERNAL) \
398 (((SYM_TARGET_INTERNAL) >> 2) & 1)
399#define ARM_SET_SYM_CMSE_SPCL(SYM_TARGET_INTERNAL) \
400 (SYM_TARGET_INTERNAL) |= 4
